Installation Process
1Ô∏è‚É£ Hardware Setup

Connect Rain Sensor Module:

VCC ‚Üí Arduino 5V

GND ‚Üí Arduino GND

AO (Analog Output) ‚Üí Arduino A0 pin

Connect Buzzer/LED:

Positive ‚Üí Arduino Digital Pin 7

Negative ‚Üí Arduino GND

(If LED, use a 220Œ© resistor in series)

2Ô∏è‚É£ Software Setup

Install Arduino IDE from Arduino Official Website.

Open Arduino IDE and select:

Board: Arduino Uno

Port: Your Arduino‚Äôs COM port (check Tools ‚Üí Port)

Copy and paste the code from your report into Arduino IDE:

// Pin Definitions
const int rainSensorPin = A0; // Analog pin connected to rain sensor
const int buzzerPin = 7;      // Optional buzzer or LED

// Rain threshold (adjust based on testing)
const int rainThreshold = 500;

void setup() {
  Serial.begin(9600);
  pinMode(rainSensorPin, INPUT);
  pinMode(buzzerPin, OUTPUT);
}

void loop() {
  int sensorValue = analogRead(rainSensorPin);

  Serial.print("Rain Sensor Reading: ");
  Serial.println(sensorValue);

  if (sensorValue < rainThreshold) {
    Serial.println("üåß Rain Detected!");
    digitalWrite(buzzerPin, HIGH); // Turn on buzzer/LED
  } else {
    Serial.println("‚òÄ No Rain.");
    digitalWrite(buzzerPin, LOW); // Turn off buzzer/LED
  }

  delay(2000); // Check every 2 seconds
}

3Ô∏è‚É£ Upload & Test

Click ‚úî Verify to compile the code.

Click ‚¨Ü Upload to send code to Arduino.

Open Serial Monitor (Ctrl+Shift+M) to see sensor readings in real-time.

Pour a small amount of water on the rain sensor ‚Äî the buzzer/LED should activate.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Calibration

Adjust the rainThreshold value in the code based on your sensor‚Äôs sensitivity.

Test in real rain or simulate with droplets to ensure accurate detection.